parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, especially at low speeds. This can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The power steering assist warning light illuminates on the dashboard
the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle loses power steering functionality
the steering wheel shakes or jerks
and the vehicle is hard to handle or turn.
